               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     <title>Mirʼāt al-khayāl</title> (Mirror of the Imagination), completed by Shīr ʻAlī Khān Lūdī (fl. 1657–90) in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1690">1103 AH (1690 CE)</date> according to a chronogram in the final line, is an encyclopedia encompassing the lives and works of 136 poets — including fifteen female authors — interspersed with treatises on varied topics such as literature, music, medicine, physics, and ethics. 
                     The author's father, 'Alī Amjad Khān (d. 1673–74), served the Mughal Prince Shāh Shuja‘ (d. 1661) in Bengal, which allowed the author to study under the poet <persName type="standard">Faraḥ Ḥusayn Nāẓim (d. 1653–64)</persName>. He subsequently found employment by the Mughal nobleman <persName>Sayyid Shukrallāh Khān, Fawjdār of Dehli</persName> in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1679">1090 AH (1679–80 CE)</date>. 
                     </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_316-item1">
                     <author key="person_314899919" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/314899919">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Lūdī, Shīr ʻAlī Khān, active 1680</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">لودی، شیر علی خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6491">Mirʼāt al-khayāl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_6491">مرآت الخيال</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">صفحه ۱: ای ز تو بند بر زبان نطق سخن سرای را *  فکر تو باعث جنون عقل گره گشای را</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">صفحه ۴۶۵: صورت تاریخ اتمامش توان بی‌ضرده دید * گر تامل پرده بردارد زمرآت الخیال</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">صفحه ۴۶۵: تمام شد نسخه مرآت الخیال من تصنیف شیر خان لودی</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Complete, with variations in comparison with the lithograph edition published by <persName role="pbl" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/316145857038622921267" key="person_316145857038622921267">Muḥammad Malik al-Kuttāb Shīrāzī</persName> in Bombay (Mumbai) in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1906">1324 AH (1906 CE)</date>. 
                        Scholar and former owner of this manuscript <persName type="standard" role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/20108923/" key="person_20108923">Nathaniel Bland (1803-1865)</persName> describes the work in his groundbreaking essay on biographies of Persian poets published in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1848">1848</date>.
                        For a complete description, see Sachau and Ethé's catalogue of the Bodleian Library, no. 374.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
